meanings.definition: The quality of being eminent or distinguished.
meanings.sent1: Her eminencies in the field of science were widely recognized.
meanings.sent2: The professor's eminencies in research led to groundbreaking discoveries.
meanings.sent3: Despite her eminencies, she remained humble and approachable.
meanings.sent4: The eminencies of the mountain range were visible from miles away.
meanings.sent5: The eminencies of her character shone through in every interaction.

meanings.definition: A position of prominence or superiority.
meanings.sent1: He reached the eminencies of his career through hard work and dedication.
meanings.sent2: The CEO's eminencies in the company were unquestionable.
meanings.sent3: The cat claimed the eminencies of the highest spot on the bookshelf.
meanings.sent4: The eminencies of the castle towered over the surrounding landscape.
meanings.sent5: The eminencies of the champion were evident in every match.
